<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>CARRIER BAG CHARGE FOR ENGLAND</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="827" height="195" alt="" style="margin-left:-103pt; margin-top:-65.5pt; position:absolute; z-index:0" /></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">Written</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Waitrose</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This document sets out Waitrose’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">response to the Environmental Audit Committee’s inquiry into a carrier bag charge for England.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">1.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Waitrose </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">welcomes the opportunity to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">respon</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">d </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Environmental Audit Committee’s inquiry </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">into </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the sustainability of measures to reduce the use of plastic shopping bags.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  The views represented are the views of Waitrose supermarkets, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a division</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of the John Lewis Partnership.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Waitrose believes that a 5p charge on single use bags will reduce bag consumption as consumers begin to change their behaviour as a result of having to pay for every bag.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since the introduction of charging in Wales in October 2011, Waitrose has seen a reduction of 76 per cent of single use bags.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">1.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Providing a free, more sustainable bag is likely to lead to increased usage, which could reverse falls in consumption as consumers begin to fall back into old habits. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">2.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">background</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our understanding is that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the existing types of biodegradable and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oxo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> degradable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bags </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">would not be exempt from the charge. Currently, only paper would be exempt and as WRAP have reported, whilst coming from a renewable source, paper requires significantly more energy to manufacture and transport than plastics and also have limited </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reuseability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We also understand that industry has been tasked with identifying a new type of biodegradable material that overcomes the main issues already identified namely: contamination of recycling stream, confusing consumers and the potential impact on existing consumer behaviour.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">response is therefore based on the knowledge currently available.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">3.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">The likely change in the number of bags discarded and any benefits for biodiversity and the environment</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">Changes in number of bags discarded</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Since charging in Wales was introduced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on ALL SINGLE USE BAGS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in October 2011, Waitrose has seen a reduction of 76 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">per cent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of single use </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">bags.  This supports the wider report produced by WRAP earlier this summer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (UK Voluntary Carrier Bag Monitoring – WRAP July 2013)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We believe a 5p charge on single use bags will reduce bag consumption as consumers start to change their behaviour as a result of having to pay for every bag.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Waitrose; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">If there was a free bag available with more ‘sustainable’ credentials, the likely increase in usage could reverse falls in consumption as consumers began to fall back into old habits.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">benefits for biodiversity and the environment</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The main problem associated with single use bags is the generation of litter.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">According to WRAP’s research, we know the majority of households (65%) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">reuse</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> their single use bags as bin liners. This would infer that the bags are either sent to landfill or for incineration and thus energy recovery.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Some consumers will recycle their bags, we offer recycling facilities in our shops, we then reuse the plastic as part of our closed loop initiatives.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">By imposing a charge on ALL single use bags, we know from evidence in Wales this results in a significant reduction of bags in circulation, therefore a charge on ALL bags would contribute towards a reduction in litter.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A charging exemption on biodegradable and degradable bags would result in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">an increase in bag consumption.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.9</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">These would still end up in either landfill or incineration as consumers will continue to use them as bin liners. Biodegradable bags (paper/natural materials) are not designed to degrade in anaerobic landfill conditions and could release methane under such conditions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Biodegradable and degradable bags should not enter the recycling stream as they contaminate the recycled content and therefore are not suitable for recycling.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.11</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The only benefit of a biodegradable bag therefore, is with regards to litter, however existing types of bio (plastic) bags still take years to decompose. We need to be changing behaviour not condoning the discarding of bags into the environment with the hope they will break down before they cause damage to marine life or unsightly litter. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt 36pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">the impact on the use of biodegradable bags and the impact on plastics recycling</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Recent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">customer research showed there is poor understanding of what biodegradable really means. When asked if consumers wanted a free biodegradable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the majority said yes, however when asked how they would dispose of the bags the majority confirmed they would continue to reuse </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">them </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as bin liners. When asked if they knew the impact on the environment could </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be detrimental, the</span><span style="font-family:Waitrose; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">majority went on to say they would prefer to pay 5p for a bag that could be recycled.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">biodegradable bag should break</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">down more quickly. If these types of bags enter the recycling stream they will compromise the quality of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">recyclant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. We have established an effective closed loop process with our plastics company. There would need to be a new process to ensure bags were segregated to reduce contamination however it is likely that recycling rates would be affected.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">any wider environmental or sustainability implications of a possible increased use of natural fibre ‘bags for life’</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">With the potential introduction of a free biodegradable bag, we would need to consider the impact on our existing range of reusable bags. We would withdraw the existing ‘recycled and recyclable’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">plastic bag as consumers would be unlikely to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pay a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 5p </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">charge if </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n alternative,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> free biodegradable bag </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is available.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">free bag option is likely to change the behaviour of those consumers who already reuse their bags as they would switch to using a free alternative.</span><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal">5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal">.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">onsumers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are more likely to move </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">away from the bag for life, which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> if used four times and recycled</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> has the lowest impact on the environment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) of Supermarket Carrier Bags 2011</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">the relative advantages and disadvantages of the proposed levy rather than a possible complete ban on lightweight plastic bags</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The proposed levy exempts biodegradable bags. By offering a free bag</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> it would continue to encourage a ‘use once’ mentality as there would </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">little incentive to remember to reuse bags. Consumers would also view the bag as a more sustainable solution to plastic, despite it not being suitable for recycling nor would it change consumers’ behaviour </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">regarding </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">disposal.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">From WRAP’s own report and LCA data, all bags should be reused as many times as possible. Biodegradable bags especially paper bags have very limited reuse opportunities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">the rationale for excluding particular types of retailer from the levy scheme</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">If the rationale for the plastic bag charge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is environmental, then its aim should be to change consumer behaviour and to encourage the reuse of bags as many times as possible.  This would not be achieved if some retailers were exempt.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Excluding some retailers would send out conflicting messages to consumers and could therefore affect the potential benefits from the charge in other areas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:110%; margin:0pt 0pt 10.5pt 35.45pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">the lessons to be learnt from other countries’ experiences in this area</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In Wales, consumers have adapted to the charge and reusing bags is commonplace as in Europe. </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">9</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">Any social or economic impacts of the proposed bag levy, for example on affordability for particular households or businesses</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There would be an enormous loss of potential funds available to charities as a result of the exemption of biodegradable bags.  In Wales, the proceeds from the 5p charge go towards social and environmental good causes. With the potential volumes available, charities stand to lose considerable funds as few retailers w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ould offer a plastic bag for 5p.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ost retailers will want to be as competitive as possible and therefore most will offer a free bio</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">degradable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> bag. If a charge was imposed on all single use bags as in Wales, the proceeds could be redirected into research and development to improve kerbside recycling/on the go recycling where the main problem lies.</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">10.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">Any </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">hygiene impacts or wider health impacts</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We are not aware of any health implications of a biodegradable or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oxo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> degradable bag. </span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">11</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">About Waitrose</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">11</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Waitrose is a national supermarket operator, operating </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">300</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">branches</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in the UK grocery market.  Waitrose also has an e-commerce grocery business (Waitrose Deliver) and an export business.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Waitrose believes that few things in life are more important than the food we buy ourselves and our families and that good, healthy food is one of life’s great pleasures.  Waitrose’s mission is to be the best quality food and wine retailer for its customers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Waitrose employs over 54,000</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> people </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">across the UK and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> all co-owners of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the John Lewis Partnership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Treading lightly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on the environment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is a commercial and environmental priority for Waitrose and a fundamental principle of the Waitrose Way.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">10 December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Times; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>